<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbb70b602-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1783"><num value="1783">§ 1783.</num><heading> Appropriations for administrative expense</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are hereby authorized to be appropriated for any fiscal year such sums as may be necessary to the Secretary for the Secretary’s administrative expense under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbb70b603-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/642/s14">Pub. L. 89–642, § 14</ref>, <date date="1966-10-11">Oct. 11, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/889">80 Stat. 889</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/101/147/tIII/s324">Pub. L. 101–147, title III, § 324</ref>, <date date="1989-11-10">Nov. 10, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/917">103 Stat. 917</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbb70b604-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbb70b605-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbb70b606-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1989—<ref href="/us/pl/101/147">Pub. L. 101–147</ref> inserted “Appropriations for administrative expense” as section catchline and substituted “are hereby” for “is hereby” and “the Secretary’s” for “his”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
